<p>The Cameron Village area, with its mix of historic and updated homes, presents unique opportunities for solar installations on homes with south-facing roofs. Crabtree Valley homes typically have larger lots and roof areas, making them ideal for substantial solar arrays. The Brier Creek area features newer construction with modern HVAC systems, but homeowners often add solar to offset higher energy usage from larger homes. Five Points and Oakwood neighborhoods contain historic homes that may require HVAC updates before solar installation to maximize the benefits of both improvements.</p>

